BRIEFING: TWO SHALLOW COLD FRONTS WILL APPROACH AND STALL NEAR KAUAI OVER THE NEXT SEVERAL DAYS. LIGHT SOUTH WINDS AHEAD OF THE FRONT WILL VEER NORTHWEST THIS EVENING. WINDS WILL REMAIN LIGHT ENOUGH OVER MAUI AND HAWAII COUNTIES TO ALLOW LAND AND SEA BREEZES TO PREVAIL. BANDS OF SHOWERS IN ADVANCE OF THE FRONT WILL PRODUCE WIDESPREAD MOUNTAIN OBSCURATION ACROSS KAUAI AND MAY SPREAD TO OAHU LATER IN THE AFTERNOON.
NO MILITARY SCHEDULED TODAY
AIRMET ZULU - NO SIGNIFICANT ICE EXP. FZLVL...151-148.
